  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study was conducted to assess the effects of an educational program that had designed
      based on teach back method in order to improve self-care competency among menopausal women.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      In this study 60 menopausal women randomly allocated to intervention group(n=30) and control
      group(n=30).

      Intervention group participated in an educational program that had designed in four sessions
      based on teach back method. Control group revived no education.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
